01:15:30.313 --> 01:15:32.271
I already decided.

1094
01:15:33.688 --> 01:15:35.146
I'm excited.

1095
01:15:40.022 --> 01:15:42.146
Oh. Saint Ruby!

1096
01:15:42.229 --> 01:15:44.438
We'll make a shrine to you on the boat.

1097
01:15:44.521 --> 01:15:45.520
Wait!

1098
01:15:45.563 --> 01:15:46.563
She's trying to help!

1099
01:15:47.063 --> 01:15:48.730
Well. thank God you have her.

1100
01:16:13.938 --> 01:16:15.855
Don't kill me.

1101
01:16:17.605 --> 01:16:23.521
I bought you a red dress for your concert.

1102
01:16:29.188 --> 01:16:31.855
If you don't like it.
you don't have to wear it.

1103
01:16:36.646 --> 01:16:39.396
I'm really glad you're staying.

1104
01:16:42.229 --> 01:16:43.646
Leo isn't.

1105
01:16:44.646 --> 01:16:45.980
It's complicated.

1106
01:16:46.354 --> 01:16:47.688
He feels...

1107
01:16:48.396 --> 01:16:49.521
left out.

1108
01:16:50.563 --> 01:16:51.897
That's crazy.

1109
01:16:53.229 --> 01:16:55.646
It's always the three of you

1110
01:16:55.730 --> 01:16:56.938
and then me.

1111
01:17:00.438 --> 01:17:02.063
I get it.

1112
01:17:11.980 --> 01:17:15.688
Do you ever wish I was deaf?

1113
01:17:28.980 --> 01:17:32.521
When you were born. at the hospital.

1114
01:17:33.730 --> 01:17:36.396
they gave you a hearing test.

1115
01:17:38.022 --> 01:17:42.354
And there you were. so tiny and sweet.

1116
01:17:44.271 --> 01:17:47.146
with these electrodes all over you.

1117
01:17:49.104 --> 01:17:51.605
And I...

1118
01:17:52.396 --> 01:17:55.438
prayed that you would be deaf.

1119
01:17:57.980 --> 01:18:00.605
When they told us

1120
01:18:00.688 --> 01:18:02.396
that you were hearing.

1121
01:18:03.605 --> 01:18:05.146
I felt...

1122
01:18:06.354 --> 01:18:08.438
My heart sank.

1123
01:18:08.521 --> 01:18:09.688
Why?

1124
01:18:10.646 --> 01:18:14.063
I was worried that we wouldn't connect.

1125
01:18:14.646 --> 01:18:16.772
Like me and my mom.

1126
01:18:16.855 --> 01:18:18.396
we're not close.

1127
01:18:19.813 --> 01:18:22.813
I thought I would fail you.

1128
01:18:23.480 --> 01:18:26.354
That being deaf would make me a bad mom.

1129
01:18:31.688 --> 01:18:32.855
Don't worry.

1130
01:18:33.563 --> 01:18:35.146
You are a bad mom

1131
01:18:35.897 --> 01:18:38.022
for so many other reasons.

1132
01:18:41.605 --> 01:18:44.730
I know I drive you crazy

1133
01:18:44.813 --> 01:18:47.480
with the clothes. the makeup.

1134
01:18:54.772 --> 01:18:56.521
But honestly.

1135
01:18:56.605 --> 01:19:00.064
I'm happy that you know who you are.

1136
01:19:02.855 --> 01:19:04.354
You're brave.

1137
01:19:04.813 --> 01:19:06.396
Not like me.

1138
01:19:51.480 --> 01:19:52.563
Get lost.

1139
01:19:53.229 --> 01:19:54.313
You hiding?

1140
01:19:55.313 --> 01:19:57.188
Not very well.

1141
01:20:02.022 --> 01:20:03.022
You still mad at me?

1142
01:20:04.855 --> 01:20:06.855
You can't fish full-time.

1143
01:20:06.938 --> 01:20:07.938
Why not?

1144
01:20:10.355 --> 01:20:11.855
Gertie told me

1145
01:20:11.938 --> 01:20:13.772
that you can really sing.

1146
01:20:14.271 --> 01:20:16.104
That's special.

1147
01:20:17.188 --> 01:20:18.772
You can't stay here.

1148
01:20:19.396 --> 01:20:22.521
They'll keep looking to you
for everything.

1149
01:20:22.605 --> 01:20:24.605
What else am I supposed to do?

1150
01:20:25.730 --> 01:20:26.897
Let me do this!

1151
01:20:26.980 --> 01:20:28.188
I got this!

1152
01:20:28.271 --> 01:20:30.022
I'm the older brother.

1153
01:20:30.104 --> 01:20:32.022
And I get treated like a baby.

1154
01:20:32.104 --> 01:20:34.647
I haven't been able to do a thing
with Fresh Catch!

1155
01:20:34.730 --> 01:20:36.730
Because it all involves
talking to hearing people!

1156
01:20:36.813 --> 01:20:38.688
So what? Who cares!

1157
01:20:38.772 --> 01:20:41.730
You're so afraid that we'd look stupid.

1158
01:20:41.813 --> 01:20:44.438
Let them figure out how to deal
with deaf people!

1159
01:20:44.939 --> 01:20:47.647
We're not helpless.

1160
01:20:50.563 --> 01:20:54.229
Our family was fine before you were born.

1161
01:20:57.939 --> 01:20:59.313
Go.

1162
01:21:09.521 --> 01:21:12.480
Come on. This is... We're not at Fenway.

1163
01:21:24.730 --> 01:21:27.647
OK. guys. you must be ready
to walk onstage in two minutes.

1164
01:21:27.730 --> 01:21:29.772
or you're not performing. OK?

1165
01:21:34.647 --> 01:21:36.064
Ruby.

1166
01:21:41.897 --> 01:21:43.980
Good evening. ladies and gentlemen!

1167
01:21:44.064 --> 01:21:46.022
For those of you who don't know.

1168
01:21:46.104 --> 01:21:49.230
I'm Bernardo Villalobos. the choir master.

1169
01:21:49.730 --> 01:21:50.855
Can you read his lips?

1170
01:21:50.939 --> 01:21:52.456
Most of these kids
call me Mr. V to my face.

1171
01:21:52.480 --> 01:21:53.521
Not really.

1172
01:21:54.230 --> 01:21:56.271
I don't know what they
call me behind my back.

1173
01:21:57.688 --> 01:21:58.915
But I'm very proud of this group.

1174
01:21:58.939 --> 01:22:00.980
They laughed.

1175
01:22:01.064 --> 01:22:02.438
They worked very hard.

1176
01:22:02.522 --> 01:22:07.647
So I will shut up now
and let you see your children.

1177
01:22:07.730 --> 01:22:09.396
which is what you came for.

1178
01:22:26.271 --> 01:22:29.563
Ain't got no troubles in my life

1179
01:22:30.647 --> 01:22:33.064
Ruby looks beautiful.

1180
01:22:33.146 --> 01:22:34.855
No foolish dreams to make me cry

1181
01:22:34.939 --> 01:22:37.230
You have good taste.

1182
01:22:37.313 --> 01:22:38.897
I'm never frightened or worried

1183
01:22:38.980 --> 01:22:42.188
I like how her red dress
matches the curtains.

1184
01:22:42.271 --> 01:22:46.730
I know I'll always get by

1185
01:22:47.605 --> 01:22:49.605
-I heat up
-Heat up

1186
01:22:49.688 --> 01:22:51.814
-I cool down
-Cool down

1187
01:22:51.897 --> 01:22:55.230
When something gets
In my way. I go round it

1188
01:22:56.104 --> 01:22:59.022
Don't let life get me down

1189
01:22:59.104 --> 01:23:00.480
She's good.

1190
01:23:02.188 --> 01:23:04.271
- She's good.
- No idea.

1191
01:23:04.355 --> 01:23:06.480
- No. she said.
- Oh!

1192
01:23:13.647 --> 01:23:15.647
I got the music in me

1193
01:23:15.730 --> 01:23:17.855
I got the music in me

1194
01:23:17.939 --> 01:23:20.980
I got the music in me

1195
01:23:25.980 --> 01:23:29.230
They say that life is a circle

1196
01:23:29.313 --> 01:23:32.188
But that ain't the way that I found it

1197
01:23:32.271 --> 01:23:33.772
I found it

1198
01:23:33.855 --> 01:23:37.271
Gonna move in a straight line

1199
01:23:37.980 --> 01:23:42.522
I leaned back on my radio

1200
01:23:42.605 --> 01:23:46.271
Some cat was laying down
Some rock and roll

1201
01:23:46.355 --> 01:23:48.313
"Lotta soul." he said

1202
01:23:55.480 --> 01:23:56.480
What's wrong?

1203
01:23:57.146 --> 01:23:58.605
My buttons are off.

1204
01:23:59.105 --> 01:24:00.897
That weren't no DJ

1205
01:24:00.980 --> 01:24:03.980
That was hazy cosmic jive

1206
01:24:06.480 --> 01:24:08.605
What do you want for dinner?

1207
01:24:09.313 --> 01:24:12.772
- Spaghetti.
- I'll have to go to the grocery store.

1208
01:24:12.855 --> 01:24:15.022
He'd like to come and meet us

1209
01:24:15.105 --> 01:24:17.271
But he thinks he'll blow our minds

1210
01:24:17.355 --> 01:24:21.605
There's a starman waiting in the sky

1211
01:24:22.772 --> 01:24:24.397
He's told us not to blow it

1212
01:24:24.480 --> 01:24:26.897
'Cause he knows it's all worthwhile

1213
01:24:26.980 --> 01:24:29.939
He told me. "Let the children lose it

1214
01:24:30.022 --> 01:24:32.647
"Let the children use it

1215
01:24:32.730 --> 01:24:35.939
Let all the children boogie"

1216
01:25:16.939 --> 01:25:19.939
And now I have a special treat.

1217
01:25:20.022 --> 01:25:23.730
Sometimes. you hear a voice. and
it reminds you to keep making music.

1218
01:25:23.814 --> 01:25:26.522
First song done. second song done.

1219
01:25:26.605 --> 01:25:31.105
Please welcome Miles Patterson
and Ruby Rossi!

1220
01:25:54.397 --> 01:25:59.105
You're all I need

1221
01:26:01.855 --> 01:26:04.981
To get by

1222
01:26:05.313 --> 01:26:08.022
Like the sweet morning dew

1223
01:26:08.105 --> 01:26:10.355
I took one look at you

1224
01:26:10.438 --> 01:26:14.814
And it was plain to see
You were my destiny

1225
01:26:15.730 --> 01:26:18.105
With my arms open wide

1226
01:26:18.188 --> 01:26:20.188
I threw away my pride

1227
01:26:20.855 --> 01:26:23.022
I'll sacrifice for you

1228
01:26:23.105 --> 01:26:25.438
Dedicate my life to you

1229
01:26:25.522 --> 01:26:28.272
I will go where you lead...

1230
01:27:37.230 --> 01:27:38.897
Go. Ruby!

1231
01:27:52.438 --> 01:27:54.856
Hey. Ruby! That was so lovely!

1232
01:27:54.939 --> 01:27:55.939
Thanks!

1233
01:27:56.022 --> 01:27:57.355
Bob!

1234
01:27:59.146 --> 01:28:00.689
Great job! Great. great job!

1235
01:28:00.772 --> 01:28:01.939
Thank you.

1236
01:28:02.022 --> 01:28:03.522
Are these your parents?

1237
01:28:03.605 --> 01:28:06.522
Yeah. Frank and Jackie.
And this is my brother. Leo.

1238
01:28:07.355 --> 01:28:12.522
This is my teacher. Mr. V. And his family.

1239
01:28:14.814 --> 01:28:15.981
Nice to fuck you.

1240
01:28:17.647 --> 01:28:19.105
I learned that on YouTube.

1241
01:28:22.814 --> 01:28:26.022
What? Isn't that. "Nice to meet you"?

1242
01:28:26.814 --> 01:28:27.814
No.

1243
01:28:28.605 --> 01:28:32.772
"Meet" is one finger. not two.
See? This is. like. the legs.

1244
01:28:32.856 --> 01:28:33.939
No!

1245
01:28:34.022 --> 01:28:35.272
No. no. no! I mean...

1246
01:28:35.355 --> 01:28:36.689
Oh my God!

1247
01:28:36.772 --> 01:28:38.272
It's fine. I get it.

1248
01:28:39.313 --> 01:28:41.230
Nice to screw you too.

1249
01:28:45.022 --> 01:28:46.772
These are my kind of parents.

1250
01:28:48.564 --> 01:28:49.689
Please tell them:

1251
01:28:49.772 --> 01:28:51.939
"Their daughter is very talented.

1252
01:28:53.522 --> 01:28:56.981
And they're making a terrible mistake
not sending her off to school."

1253
01:28:58.188 --> 01:28:59.856
I'll just sign the first part.

1254
01:28:59.939 --> 01:29:03.188
I'm meeting Miles at his audition
tomorrow. You still have your slot.

1255
01:29:03.272 --> 01:29:05.147
- What is he saying?
- You have to stop.

1256
01:29:05.230 --> 01:29:06.814
OK. OK.

1257
01:29:06.897 --> 01:29:08.647
But thank you.

1258
01:29:35.605 --> 01:29:39.064
I'm gonna get some air.

1259
01:29:39.564 --> 01:29:40.731
Okay.

1260
01:29:53.105 --> 01:29:55.022
What's up?

1261
01:29:56.605 --> 01:29:58.522
Just thinking.

1262
01:30:02.230 --> 01:30:06.439
The stars here.

1263
01:30:06.522 --> 01:30:11.439
they don't look as good as
they do on the water.

1264
01:30:26.272 --> 01:30:31.647
The song you sang tonight.
What was it about?

1265
01:30:38.105 --> 01:30:40.147
It was about...

1266
01:30:41.856 --> 01:30:45.272
what it is to need another person.

1267
01:30:48.397 --> 01:30:52.439
Can you sing it for me?

1268
01:30:53.439 --> 01:30:54.647
Now?

1269
01:30:54.731 --> 01:30:56.313
Please.

1270
01:31:07.897 --> 01:31:10.814
Like the sweet morning dew

1271
01:31:12.731 --> 01:31:16.564
I took one look at you

1272
01:31:17.564 --> 01:31:20.939
And it was plain to see

1273
01:31:21.023 --> 01:31:24.647
You were my destiny

1274
01:31:25.814 --> 01:31:28.856
With my arms open wide

1275
01:31:28.939 --> 01:31:33.064
Louder. More!

1276
01:31:33.147 --> 01:31:36.188
I'll sacrifice for you

1277
01:31:36.272 --> 01:31:40.564
Dedicate my life to you

1278
01:31:41.939 --> 01:31:45.314
I will go where you lead

1279
01:31:45.397 --> 01:31:48.564
Always there in time of need

1280
01:31:48.647 --> 01:31:52.147
And when I lose my will

1281
01:31:52.230 --> 01:31:55.064
You'll be there to push me up the hill

1282
01:31:55.147 --> 01:31:57.272
There's no

1283
01:31:57.731 --> 01:32:02.856
No looking back for us

1284
01:32:02.939 --> 01:32:07.105
We got love sure enough

1285
01:32:07.188 --> 01:32:09.064
That's enough

1286
01:32:09.355 --> 01:32:11.814
You're all

1287
01:32:12.105 --> 01:32:16.023
All that I need

1288
01:32:18.856 --> 01:32:22.314
To get by

1289
01:32:55.105 --> 01:32:56.480
Are we fishing?

1290
01:32:56.564 --> 01:32:57.564
No.

1291
01:33:14.230 --> 01:33:16.314
You guys. this is ridiculous!

1292
01:33:16.606 --> 01:33:20.606
If we're kicking you out.
we're all doing it as a family.

1293
01:33:44.189 --> 01:33:46.105
Maybe over there?

1294
01:34:03.314 --> 01:34:05.023
I'm gonna park.

1295
01:34:12.731 --> 01:34:14.814
Look how they're dressed.

1296
01:34:14.898 --> 01:34:16.439
It's so different.

1297
01:34:17.023 --> 01:34:19.481
It's fine. You look pretty.

1298
01:34:20.939 --> 01:34:22.439
Hey! I'm here for my audition.

1299
01:34:22.522 --> 01:34:23.439
OK! What's your name?

1300
01:34:23.522 --> 01:34:25.023
Ruby Rossi.

1301
01:34:26.689 --> 01:34:28.856
It looks like you're
about half an hour late.

1302
01:34:28.939 --> 01:34:30.355
Are you ready to go?

1303
01:34:33.023 --> 01:34:34.522
We roll deep.

1304
01:34:34.856 --> 01:34:36.898
I'm sorry. Your family
can't go in with you.

1305
01:34:38.147 --> 01:34:39.522
What did she say?

1306
01:34:40.023 --> 01:34:41.481
You can't go in.

1307
01:34:52.397 --> 01:34:53.397
Ruby!

1308
01:34:53.481 --> 01:34:54.481
Hey!

1309
01:34:54.564 --> 01:34:55.439
You came!

1310
01:34:55.522 --> 01:34:56.689
Is Mr. V here?

1311
01:34:56.773 --> 01:34:59.272
He just left. I can call him.

1312
01:34:59.355 --> 01:35:01.773
I texted him. How did it go?

1313
01:35:03.397 --> 01:35:04.939
I choked.

1314
01:35:05.023 --> 01:35:06.064
What?

1315
01:35:06.147 --> 01:35:07.564
Ruby Rossi?

1316
01:35:21.856 --> 01:35:23.272
Hello there!

1317
01:35:23.355 --> 01:35:24.397
Hi.

1318
01:35:25.023 --> 01:35:26.773
You are...

1319
01:35:26.856 --> 01:35:29.272
Ruby. Ruby Rossi.

1320
01:35:31.230 --> 01:35:33.023
OK. Ruby Rossi.

1321
01:35:33.856 --> 01:35:35.731
Looking at your application.

1322
01:35:35.814 --> 01:35:38.481
aside from your involvement
in the school choir

1323
01:35:38.564 --> 01:35:42.397
and a very nice letter
from Bernardo Villalobos.

1324
01:35:42.981 --> 01:35:45.773
you don't have a lot
of history with music.

1325
01:35:51.023 --> 01:35:53.147
I don't under... Is there a question?

1326
01:36:03.481 --> 01:36:07.105
Let's go upstairs.

1327
01:36:17.689 --> 01:36:19.981
What is your first song today?

1328
01:36:20.564 --> 01:36:22.564
Both Sides. Now by Joni Mitchell.

1329
01:36:22.647 --> 01:36:24.314
Do you have your sheet music?

1330
01:36:27.564 --> 01:36:29.647
I don't. I forgot.

1331
01:36:32.356 --> 01:36:34.230
Do you know that song?

1332
01:36:35.814 --> 01:36:38.898
All right. You are just going
to have to sing it a cappella.

1333
01:36:41.648 --> 01:36:42.648
OK.

1334
01:36:44.564 --> 01:36:46.397
I can accompany her.

1335
01:36:47.856 --> 01:36:50.105
Sorry for interrupting. Hi!

1336
01:36:51.230 --> 01:36:52.439
How are you?

1337
01:36:52.522 --> 01:36:56.439
I'm Bernardo Villalobos. class of '89.

1338
01:36:57.147 --> 01:36:58.189
Nice to see you all.

1339
01:36:59.564 --> 01:37:01.356
May I?

1340
01:37:03.648 --> 01:37:05.147
I guess so.

1341
01:37:05.230 --> 01:37:06.981
Thank you.

1342
01:37:07.065 --> 01:37:08.272
What is going on?

1343
01:37:27.648 --> 01:37:32.856
Rows and flows of angel hair

1344
01:37:32.940 --> 01:37:38.522
And ice cream castles in the air

1345
01:37:39.023 --> 01:37:40.856
And feather can...

1346
01:37:45.814 --> 01:37:47.522
Sorry. My mistake.

1347
01:37:50.773 --> 01:37:52.564
Can we take it from the top?

1348
01:38:14.023 --> 01:38:18.981
Rows and flows of angel hair

1349
01:38:19.065 --> 01:38:24.814
And ice cream castles in the air

1350
01:38:24.898 --> 01:38:30.564
And feather canyons everywhere

1351
01:38:31.314 --> 01:38:34.606
I've looked at clouds that way

1352
01:38:37.023 --> 01:38:41.356
But now they only block the sun

1353
01:38:41.439 --> 01:38:47.439
They rain and snow on everyone

1354
01:38:47.523 --> 01:38:53.648
So many things I would have done

1355
01:38:53.731 --> 01:38:59.147
But clouds got in my way

1356
01:38:59.689 --> 01:39:03.898
I've looked at clouds
From both sides now

1357
01:39:04.523 --> 01:39:07.439
From up and down

1358
01:39:07.523 --> 01:39:10.147
And still somehow

1359
01:39:10.231 --> 01:39:15.773
It's cloud illusions I recall

1360
01:39:15.856 --> 01:39:21.481
I really don't know clouds

1361
01:39:25.523 --> 01:39:27.356
At all

1362
01:39:30.981 --> 01:39:35.689
Moons and Junes and Ferris wheels

1363
01:39:35.773 --> 01:39:41.023
The dizzy dancing way you feel

1364
01:39:41.105 --> 01:39:47.523
As every fairy tale comes real

1365
01:39:47.606 --> 01:39:51.564
I've looked at love that way

1366
01:39:53.397 --> 01:39:57.940
But now it's just another show

1367
